cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.NA 

The paper deals with encoding images and videos, and improving classification performance by considering the Riemannian geometry of the resulting space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of dictionary learning and sparse coding also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The optimization of the kernel-based projection space suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
